<paragraph id="9979FA25FFE9933BBC9BFB297F39F8B7" blockId="1.[151,1437,1246,2027]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis id="ABB22637FFE9933BBC9BFB297AB8FB53" bold="true" box="[151,413,1246,1271]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Medium sized cixiid: body length 
<quantity id="5E3E57C0FFE9933BBF32FB2978EDFB52" box="[830,968,1246,1271]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.85" metricValueMax="7.2" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" unit="mm" value="5.85" valueMax="7.2" valueMin="4.5">4.5–7.2 mm</quantity>
in males, 4.0– 
<quantity id="5E3E57C0FFE9933BB87AFB297FEBFB52" box="[1142,1230,1246,1271]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
in females. Body laterally compressed. Frons long, wider than vertex in middle, evenly rounded in lateral view, lacking transverse carina on dorsal border; median carina weakly marked; lateral carinae strongly produced and directed obliquely laterally (
<figureCitation id="01FDE6A0FFE9933BBD0EFABD7A43FAC7" box="[258,358,1354,1379]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,519,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1428,519,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Amazobenna reticulata Penny: 1. Male habitus, lateral view; 2. Female, habitus, lateral view; 3. Male head, anterior view; 4. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Male antenna, lateral view; 6. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm. Specimen from Amazonas, Manaus, highway AM 010, Km 54." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632445/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Figs. 3,4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="01FDE6A0FFE9933BBD7FFABC7A98FAC7" box="[371,445,1355,1379]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Amazobenna pennyi sp. nov., holotype: 19. Habitus, lateral view; 20. Head, anterior view; 21. Antenna, lateral view; 22. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 23. Abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632453/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">20, 22</figureCitation>
). Clypeus with median carina low, little evident, much lower than lateral carinae; lateral carinae strongly produced. Ocelli distinct. Scapus short, pedicellus cylindrical, as long as wide to slightly longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="01FDE6A0FFE9933BBD16FA657A48FA0F" box="[282,365,1426,1451]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,519,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1428,519,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Amazobenna reticulata Penny: 1. Male habitus, lateral view; 2. Female, habitus, lateral view; 3. Male head, anterior view; 4. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Male antenna, lateral view; 6. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm. Specimen from Amazonas, Manaus, highway AM 010, Km 54." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632445/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="01FDE6A0FFE9933BBD70FA647ABEFA0F" box="[380,411,1427,1451]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Amazobenna pennyi sp. nov., holotype: 19. Habitus, lateral view; 20. Head, anterior view; 21. Antenna, lateral view; 22. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 23. Abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632453/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">21</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with dorsal longitudinal carina distinct. Mesonotum with median and lateral longitudinal carinae present, but sometimes lateral carinae weakly marked (
<figureCitation id="01FDE6A0FFE9933BBFEFFA417F17FA6B" box="[995,1074,1462,1487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,519,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1428,519,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Amazobenna reticulata Penny: 1. Male habitus, lateral view; 2. Female, habitus, lateral view; 3. Male head, anterior view; 4. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Male antenna, lateral view; 6. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm. Specimen from Amazonas, Manaus, highway AM 010, Km 54." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632445/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="01FDE6A0FFE9933BB832FA407F7BFA6B" box="[1086,1118,1463,1487]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Amazobenna pennyi sp. nov., holotype: 19. Habitus, lateral view; 20. Head, anterior view; 21. Antenna, lateral view; 22. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 23. Abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632453/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">22</figureCitation>
). Fore wings long, widening distally, exceeding apex of abdomen for about half of the total length, apical margin round (Figs. 28,29). Cubital veins strongly curved toward anal margin of wing, reaching edge of wing at an almost straight angle. First cell of cubitus about ten times longer than wide. Metatibia with 6–7 apical spines; tarsus with 7+7–8 apical spines. Abdominal pleura of four and five segments with a process bearing 3 + 2 sensory pits, with one furcate seta each (
<figureCitation id="01FDE6A0FFE9933BBC93F99D7BD1F927" box="[159,244,1642,1667]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,519,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1428,519,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Amazobenna reticulata Penny: 1. Male habitus, lateral view; 2. Female, habitus, lateral view; 3. Male head, anterior view; 4. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Male antenna, lateral view; 6. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm. Specimen from Amazonas, Manaus, highway AM 010, Km 54." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632445/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="01FDE6A0FFE9933BBD0BF99C7A02F927" box="[263,295,1643,1667]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,369,1871]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Amazobenna pennyi sp. nov., holotype: 19. Habitus, lateral view; 20. Head, anterior view; 21. Antenna, lateral view; 22. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 23. Abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 1= 1mm; 2,4 = 0.5mm; 3 = 0.3 mm; 5 = 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2632453/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">23</figureCitation>
). Male terminalia: pygofer symmetrical, elongate and somewhat triangular in lateral view; anal segment rectangular in dorsal view; medioventral process conical in lateral view; genital styles elongate, symmetrical, curved upward; aedeagus robust with shaft and flagellum well developed, bearing long thorn-shaped processes. Female genitalia like in other Bennarellini: ovipositor elongate, orthopteroid, and curved upwards, 9th tergite without wax plate, gonapophysis IX medially fused and bearing spinules.
</paragraph>
